cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper discusses solutions to ranking search results in a genealogy search engine, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract information from historical records, which falls under cs.CL. The use of various types of records and the need to combine them for ranking suggests the involvement of database (DB) techniques, placing cs.DB as the third likely sub-category. The proposed algorithms, customized coordinate ascent and stochastic search, involve machine learning (ML) techniques, which fall under cs.AI and cs.LG.
